text: Limnonectes hikidai is a species of fanged frogs in the family Dicroglossidae. It is endemic to Sarawak, Malaysia. Its type locality is Mount Serapi in Kubah National Park, Matang, Kuching District, Sarawak, Malaysia. It is closely related to Limnonectes cintalubang. ==References== *Matsui and Nishikawa, 2014, Curr. Herpetol., Kyoto, 33: 138. Holotype: KUHE 17212, by original designation.
